  "$4,600": "",
  "$3,000": "",
  "$5,000": "",
  "R(100) = integral from 0 to 100 of (50-0.4x) dx = [50x - 0.2x^2] from 0 to 100 = 5000 - 2000 = $3,000.": "",
  "A patient receives medication at a rate of r(t) = 20/(1+t) mg per hour. How much medication is administered in the first 3 hours?": "",
  "60 mg, based in": "",
  "15 mg when considering all": "",
  "20*ln(4), approximately 27.7 mg": "",
  "20 mg, even when conditions": "",
  "integral from 0 to 3 of 20/(1+t) dt = 20*ln|1+t| from 0 to 3 = 20*(ln 4 - ln 1) = 20*ln(4), which is about 27.7 mg.": "",
  "Snow falls at a rate of s(t) = 2t inches per hour. After 5 hours, a snowplow begins clearing. How much snow accumulated in the first 5 hours?": "",
  "25 inches": "",
  "10 inches": "",
  "50 inches": "",
  "5 inches": "",
  "integral from 0 to 5 of 2t dt = [t^2] from 0 to 5 = 25 inches.": "",
  "Electricity is consumed at a rate of P(t) = 100 + 50*sin(pi*t/12) watts for t in hours. How many watt-hours are used in a full 24-hour period?": "",
  "2,400 watt-hours": "",
  "3,600 watt-hours": "",
  "1,200 watt-hours": "",
  "4,800 watt-hours": "",
  "integral from 0 to 24 of [100+50sin(pi*t/12)] dt. The sine term integrates to 0 over a full period (24 hours = 2 periods). So the answer is 100*24 = 2,400 Wh.": "",
  "A city's population grows at a rate of dP/dt = 500 + 20t people per year. If the population is 50,000 at t = 0, what is it after 10 years?": "",
  "60,000 people": "",
  "57,000 people": "",
  "56,000 people": "",
  "55,000 people": "",
  "Population increase = integral from 0 to 10 of (500+20t) dt = [500t+10t^2] from 0 to 10 = 5000+1000 = 6000. Total: 50000+6000 = 56,000.": ""
